paragraphs.title: save files
paragraphs.text:
new File(tmpFolder).mkdirs
def save(names: String*) = names.map { (name) =>
    val contents = Source.fromURL(
        s"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datacharmer/test_db/master/load_$name.dump").mkString
    val records = contents.split("\n").map(_.
        replaceAll(
            "(INSERT.*VALUES|\\(|\\),|\\)|'|;)","").
                trim).filter(_ != "").mkString("\n")
    val fileName = s"$tmpFolder/$name.csv"
    new PrintWriter(fileName) { 
        write(records); 
        close 
    }
    fileName
}

save("departments", "dept_emp", "dept_manager", "employees", "salaries1", "salaries2", "salaries3", "titles")

case class Department(id: String, name: String)
case class DepartmentEmployee(employeeId: String, departmentId: String, activeFrom: String, activeTo: String)
case class DepartmentManager(employeeId: String, departmentId: String, activeFrom: String, activeTo: String)
case class Employee(id: String, dob: String, firstName: String, lastName: String, gender: String, hireDate: String)
case class EmployeeSalary(employeeId: String, salary: String, activeFrom: String, activeTo: String)
case class EmployeeTitle(employeeId: String, title: String, activeFrom: String, activeTo: String)

def read[T:ClassTag](tmpFolder: String)(name: String, constructor: Seq[String] => T) = {
    sc.textFile(s"$tmpFolder/$name.csv").map(_.split(",")).map(constructor(_))
}

def fromTemp[T:ClassTag](name: String, constructor: Seq[String] => T) = read[T](tmpFolder)(name, constructor)

def reg(df: DataFrame, tableName: String) = { df.registerTempTable(tableName); (tableName -> df) }

val csvToSalary = (vals: Seq[String]) => {
    EmployeeSalary(vals(0), vals(1), vals(2), vals(3))
}

val tableDataFrames = Map(
    reg(fromTemp("departments", (vals: Seq[String]) => Department(vals(0), vals(1))).toDF, 
        "department"),
    reg(fromTemp("dept_emp", (vals: Seq[String]) => DepartmentEmployee(vals(0), vals(1), vals(2), vals(3))).toDF, 
        "department_employee"),
    reg(fromTemp("dept_manager", (vals: Seq[String]) => DepartmentManager(vals(0), vals(1), vals(2), vals(3))).toDF, 
        "department_manager"),
    reg(fromTemp("employees", (vals: Seq[String]) => Employee(vals(0), vals(1), vals(2), vals(3), vals(4), vals(5))).toDF, 
        "employee"),
    reg(fromTemp("salaries1", csvToSalary).union(fromTemp("salaries2", csvToSalary)).union(fromTemp("salaries3", csvToSalary)).toDF, 
        "employee_salary"),
    reg(fromTemp("titles", (vals: Seq[String]) => EmployeeTitle(vals(0), vals(1), vals(2), vals(3))).toDF, 
        "employee_title"))
    
sqlContext.cacheTable("department")

paragraphs.title: Employed & Salary by Gender
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select days.value as day, gender, count(*) as employed, avg(salary.salary) as salary from days
cross join employee
join employee_salary salary on
    salary.employeeId = employee.id
    and salary.activeFrom <= days.value
    and salary.activeTo > days.value
group by days.value, gender
order by days.value, gender

paragraphs.title: Average Duration of Employment by Gender
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select days.value as day, gender, avg(dateDiff(date(days.value), date(hireDate))) as avg_length_employment, count(*), sum(dateDiff(date(days.value), date(hireDate))) from days, employee
where hireDate <= days.value
and days.value < (select max(activeTo) from employee_salary where employeeId = id)
group by days.value, gender
order by days.value, gender

%sql
select days.value, avg(dateDiff(date(days.value), date(emps.hireDate))) as avg_length_employment, count(emps.*) from (
    select '1999-12-31' as hireDate from dual
    union
    select '2001-12-31' as hireDate from dual
    union
    select '2002-07-22' as hireDate from dual
) as emps
cross join days
where emps.hireDate <= days.value
group by days.value
order by days.value

paragraphs.title: load views
paragraphs.text:
val allDataFrames = tableDataFrames + ("employees_vw" -> sqlContext.sql(s"""
    select emp.id, emp.firstName, emp.lastName, emp.dob, emp.gender, emp.hireDate,
        title.title, ed.name as department, nvl(md.name, 'N/A') as manages, 
        salary.salary from employee emp
    join employee_title title on
        title.employeeId = emp.id
        and title.activeFrom <= $today
        and title.activeTo > $today
    join department_employee on
        department_employee.employeeId = emp.id
        and department_employee.activeFrom <= $today
        and department_employee.activeTo > $today
    join department ed on
        ed.id = department_employee.departmentId
    left join department_manager mgr on
        mgr.employeeId = emp.id
        and mgr.activeFrom <= $today
        and mgr.activeTo > $today
    left join department md on
        md.id = mgr.departmentId
    join employee_salary salary on
        salary.employeeId = emp.id
        and salary.activeFrom <= $today
        and salary.activeTo > $today
"""))

allDataFrames("employees_vw").registerTempTable("employees_vw")
